CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 19, 1954, page 21, reads: "Shown here is the winner of the Ken-L-Products Division, the Quaker Oats Company's boxer puppy, Mrs. James Jones. The puppy was presented by District Representative Robert D. Crossett."
TitMainTitle: Two men, including District Representative Robert D. Crossett on left, and Mrs. James Jones, holding a boxer puppy, standing on stage in Hunt Armory for thr 1954 Pittsburgh Courier Home Service Fair
